webpackJsonp([47885229563537],{363:function(t,e){t.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>Snapchat is trying to be something that it isn’t. It isn’t a place for amassing the largest audience possible. Leave that to Instagram.\nPeople are complaining about discoverability on Snapchat. Is that what you really want from Snapchat? Isn’t it enough to be able to share the fun (or not so fun) moments with just your close friends?</p>\n<p>People need to get out of their addiction mindset and start building more relationships.</p>\n<p>I’ve recently been hearing a lot about how Snapchat is dying and how Instagram stories are the best thing. They’re probably right, but I’m still not happy about it. Snapchat was the first social media platform that I actually found myself using from time to time. As a person who very strongly values having a strong personal connection to the people I interact with, most social media sites never hit their mark. All of them focused on reaching as massive of an audience as possible so the maximum number of people can hear the mass-produced bullshit that tickles their willies.</p>\n<p>When I use Snapchat, most of the time, I’m sending directly to the people I</p>\n<p>The only reason I view the stories is to get rid of the purple icon at the bottom. It’s mostly just clicking through them becaise I don’t really care.</p>\n<p>One of the overarching themes that I see in Snapchat haters is that the interface is confusing and “user hostile.”</p>\n<p>I love Snapchat’s interface! They actually tried to do something new! Trying to innovate</p>\n<p>It’s unfortunate that</p>\n<p>At the risk of sounding like some sort of luddite, I’ve never liked Facebook, I’ve never liked Twitter, I’ve never liked Google+ (I guess that was everyone though), and I’ve never liked Instagram. If you go to my <a href="/contact">contact page</a>, you’ll see each of these listed as something that I tried because, at the very least, I find it important to</p>\n<p>My personal brand is that I care about people.</p>\n<p>The only solidarity I have in writing this blog is that probably nobody is going to read it except for the people I know in person.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"Story Wars",tags:["stories","social"]}}},pathContext:{slug:"snapchat"}}}});
